# {{ .TitleName }} — devedge micro-frontend

An Angular 15 + single-spa micro-frontend wired to the open-core
[`devedge-ufe-sdk`](https://github.com/infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-sdk). Generated
by `de ufe new {{ .Name }}` — **correct on first run**. There are no
placeholders to rename: the app id, package name, nav group, and route are all
already `{{ .AppID }}`.

## What you get, and why it works on the first run

- **Nav renders immediately.** The default nav item in `src/metadata.ts` uses
  group `{{ .AppID }}`, which is registered in the dev `GroupRegistry`, and
  `assertNavContributions(...)` runs at import — a wrong group would fail LOUD
  at startup, never render nothing silently.
- **The route matches.** The app route (`app-routing.module.ts`), the manifest
  `routes` (`metadata.ts`), and the nav item `path` all agree on `/{{ .AppID }}`.
  No accidental `path: ''` that never activates.
- **Auth is wired.** `main.ufe.ts` bootstraps `AppModule` with
  `platformBrowserDynamic`, so it provides the shell-owned `SessionProvider`
  into Angular DI as a platform `StaticProvider`:
  `{ provide: SESSION_PROVIDER, useValue: props.session }`. (The alternative
  `provideDevedgeSession(props.session)` returns `EnvironmentProviders` and is
  the path for a standalone `bootstrapApplication(...)` app — it is not usable
  as a `platformBrowserDynamic` StaticProvider. Either way the injected token
  is identical.) HttpClient is registered with the `bearerAuthInterceptor`, so
  API calls carry the Bearer token. This uFE never authenticates — the shell
  owns OIDC.
- **Local dev round-trips out of the box.** A devedge-sdk service runs the dev
  authorizer, which reads raw `account-id`/`groups` metadata — not a bearer
  token — so the bearer interceptor alone gets `PermissionDenied` in local dev.
  `AppModule` also registers `devAuthInterceptor`, which stamps the identity
  headers from `environment.devAuthHeaders` (`account-id: t1`, `groups: admin`)
  onto same-origin API calls. Edit those values for your tenant. It is a no-op
  in production (`environment.prod.ts` leaves `devAuthHeaders` empty), where
  real OIDC and the bearer token take over.
- **The webpack/`angular.json` wiring is clean.** A single
  `@angular-builders/custom-webpack:browser` build using `extra-webpack.config.js`;
  no dead `single-spa` architect targets pointing at a non-existent
  `webpack.config`.

## Install

The open-core `@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-*` packages are published to **GitHub
Packages** (public). GitHub requires a token to install even public npm
packages, so set `GITHUB_TOKEN` to a PAT with the `read:packages` scope — any
GitHub account can create one; it is **not** gated on Infoblox org membership.
The generated `.npmrc` already points the `@infobloxopen` scope at GitHub
Packages; everything else installs anonymously from npmjs.

```sh
export GITHUB_TOKEN=<a PAT with read:packages>   # https://github.com/settings/tokens
pnpm install     # (or npm install) — resolves @infobloxopen/* from GitHub Packages
```

**Working on the SDK itself?** Link a local checkout instead of the registry —
no token needed:

```sh
# From a clone of infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-sdk, built with `pnpm -r build`.
# Run these here (in the uFE project); adjust the path to your checkout:
SDK=../devedge-ufe-sdk/packages
pnpm add "@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-core@link:$SDK/core" \
  "@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-angular@link:$SDK/angular" \
  "@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-single-spa@link:$SDK/single-spa" \
  "@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-oidc@link:$SDK/oidc" \
  "@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-dev-loop@link:$SDK/dev-loop"
```

## Local dev loop

```sh
pnpm start                 # ng serve on http://localhost:{{ .DevPort }}
pnpm run doctor            # devedge-ufe doctor: loud checklist, not a silent fail
```

`doctor` runs the open-core `devedge-ufe doctor` against the dev server and
reports the FIRST failing step (reachability → TLS cert trust → CORS →
manifest → nav groups) with an actionable message. The scaffold's dev server
serves plain `http`, so `doctor` and the `--url` in `package.json` both use
`http://localhost:{{ .DevPort }}` and the TLS-cert step passes trivially.

> **If you serve over `https`,** trust the dev cert or the shell fails to load
> this uFE **silently** — add it to your keychain, or set `NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS`
> to its path. Point `doctor` at the `https://` URL so it isolates a cert
> problem as its own step instead of a generic network error.

To point a running shell at this local bundle, use the import-map override:

```ts
import { override } from '@infobloxopen/devedge-ufe-dev-loop';
override('{{ .AppID }}', 'http://localhost:{{ .DevPort }}/main.js');
```

## Build & deploy

```sh
pnpm build                 # UMD bundle → dist/{{ .AppID }}/
```

The base scaffold ships a generic static-bundle `Dockerfile`, a minimal
`deploy/manifest.yaml`, and a `charts/{{ .AppID }}-ufe/` Helm chart. Anything
beyond that generic deploy chart is provided by a preset overlaid with
`--preset-dir` (a downstream extension point; the public scaffold ships none).

## Layout

```
package.json            deps (no Angular-2-era deadweight, no committed lockfile)
angular.json            custom-webpack browser build (no dead single-spa targets)
extra-webpack.config.js UMD entries + permissive-CORS dev server
tsconfig*.json          TS config
src/main.ufe.ts         single-spa entry; provides the session into Angular DI
src/metadata.ts         validated manifest; default nav group + matching route
src/polyfills.ts        zone.js + core-js
src/app/                app.module, app.component, routing, home
Dockerfile              static-bundle image
deploy/manifest.yaml    minimal Deployment + Service
charts/{{ .AppID }}-ufe/ minimal Helm chart
```
